"Ethernet address 00:00:5e:00:53:00" ether host 00:00:5e:00:53:00
"Ethernet type 0x0806 (ARP)" ether proto 0x0806
"No Broadcast and no Multicast" not broadcast and not multicast
"No ARP" not arp
"No ARP and no DNS" not arp and port not 53
"Captures VLAN traffic for a particular host." vlan and host 192.168.1.1
"Captures VLAN traffic for a paticular host and a particular port (HTTP in the example)" vlan and (host 192.168.1.1 and port 80)
"Capture PPPOE traffic" pppoes and (host 192.168.1.1 and port 80)
"Captures PPPOE traffic for a paticular host and a particular port (HTTP in the example)" pppoes and host 192.168.1.1
"IPv4 only" ip
"IPv4 address 192.0.2.1" host 192.0.2.1
"Capture only traffic to or from a specific IP address" host 192.168.1.1
"Capture traffic to or from (sources or destinations) a range of IP addresses." net 192.168.1.0 mask 255.255.255.0
"Capture traffic to or from (sources or destinations) a range of IP addresses" src net 192.168.1.0/24
"Capture traffic to or from (sources or destinations) a range of IP addresses" dst net 192.168.1.0/24
"IPv6 only" ip6
"IPv6 address 2001:db8::1" host 2001:db8::1
"Capture IPv6 Native Traffic Only.  This will exclude tunnelled IPv6"  ip6 and not ip proto 41
"Capture only IPv6 over IPv4 Tunnelled Traffic" ip proto 41
"Capture traffic within a range of ports"  tcp portrange 1800-1880
"Captures all IPv6 traffic within the local network that is multicast (such as Neighbor and Router advertisements)" dst host ff02::1 
"TCP only" tcp
"UDP only" udp
"Non-DNS" not port 53
"TCP or UDP port 80 (HTTP)" port 80
"HTTP TCP port (80)" tcp port http
"Non-HTTP and non-SMTP to/from www.wireshark.org" not port 80 and not port 25 and host www.wireshark.org
"Capture only FTP Traffic"  tcp portrange 20-21
"Captures VoIP SIP traffic using TCP" tcp port sip
"Captures VoIP SIP traffic using UDP" udp port sip
